<br>
Wow...ignorance abounds...<br>
<br>
It makes me sick that those that try to live a compassionate way of life get sh*t on time and time again.<br>
<br>
So you people know, I did alot of research before I chose vegetarianism. Knowledge is power, my friends, and I suggest you get some before you start flapping your gums about something you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> obviously</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> know nothing about. I don't have a bus, but if I did, I could drive it through the holes in some of the arguments in this thread today. <br>
<br>
First of all, I (and most veggies, I'm sure) am (are) sick of the &quot;Plants die too&quot; Arguement. <br>
<br>
So, just becuase we can't stop all of the suffering in the world doesn't mean we shouldn't stop what is in our power to? Psshh... weak, weak, weak. If you are going to insult vegetarianism, don't be a sheep, think of something we haven't heard a million times.<br>
<br>
PETA:<br>
<br>
 Umm...I'll tell you that all vegetarians aren't members of this organization and don't necessarily agree with the way they do things. As far as I am concerned, PETA is a bunch of fear mongers and they do more scaring people away with their tactics than educating on the subject of vegetarianism. The sure as Hell don't get <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> my</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> money or membership.<br>
<br>
Just plain and simple insults:<br>
<br>
Some of it made me pissed, some of it made me laugh (ignorance factor), and some of it hurt me, because it came from people that I thought were respectful people in general. I guess I know now. Thanks for the eye-opener. <br>
<br>
Oh, and in referrence to this:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;So you are against the exploitation of animals for corporate or consumer gain?&quot;<br>
<br>
She responded: &quot;Yes. All of you should.&quot;<br>
<br>
To which he responded: &quot;So what type of plant did you get your suede jacket, leather boots and leather handbag from?&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This person in this story is a Grade A moron and in no way represents the bulk of the vegetarian population. There are stupid people in all groups, why should vegetarianism be any different?<br>
<br>
There is alot more, but frankly, I don't have the energy, time or layers of skin on my fingers to combat it all.<br>
<br>
I did, however found some intelligent statements in the thread. A few of them, include:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> About 2/3rds of my staff were Vegetarians. A handful were vegans. They were all great folks, we just agreed not to preach at each other. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
What? You mean you don't berate each other for your personal decisions? Wow...how very <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> mature</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. This is a good lesson for alot of you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I'm not a vegan, I really like to eat meat, but I do think animals whether they are pets or a food source should be treated as ethically and humanely as possible.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
*nods*<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Human beings are adaptable, we adapt to our surrondings fast and hence we can eat vegetables and meat and actually live rather well of either one. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Mmm Hmm...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The thing that bugs me about -most- vegans and vegetarians (even the modified ones) is that they assume you won't eat something vegetarian or vegan and/or that you will insist on having meat. It also bugs me that they refer to those who eat meat as carnivores. umm... No... I am an OMNIVORE thank you very much.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes, you certainly are an omnivore, Calliou. And class, please take notes on Calliou's useage of the word <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> most</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
This indicates that this statement does not apply to the vegetarian population as a whole and shows <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> intelligence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on the part of Calliou.<br>
<br>
Alright, I'm done b*tching about something I know you people deon't care about and go back to being the quiet, non-flaming Cielo that you all have come to expect me to be. Just do me one favor. Put this thread in another context. What if the title had been &quot;Christians can eat me&quot; or something similar?Insert your religious, ethnic or political group in there, then think of how you would feel about this thread. I am not trying to change people's minds about being vegetarian; eat what you will. *shrugs* I only ask that you not insult the group as a whole becasue they hold different opinions and values than you. I have aTON of non-veggie freinds. Do I insult them for eating meat? Of course not. I repsect the decsions they make and they respect mine. <br>
<br>
Blah... I'm done. <br>
